The paper proposes a new architecture for demand forecasting using spatiotemporal data. The proposed architecture utilizes graph networks and temporal-guided embedding to extract complex spatiotemporal patterns in data. The paper also discusses the use of long-term histories to consider periodicity and seasonality patterns as time series data. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
